@startuml

title User Status Change Email Notification Sequence Diagram

actor "Super Admin" as Admin

participant "Frontend (Website)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "UserController" as UC
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
  participant "Email Service" as EmailService
  participant "GenericMail Mailable" as GenericMail
end box

participant "Laravel Mail Queue / SMTP" as Mailer
participant "Gmail" as Gmail
database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of Admin
It is assumed the Admin is
authenticated/authorized unless an exception occurs.
end note

== Update User Status and Trigger Email ==

Admin -> FE: Change user status to "Bloqueado" or "Activo"
activate Admin
activate FE
activate Apache
activate MW
activate UC
activate ORM
activate EmailService
activate GenericMail
activate Mailer
activate Gmail
activate DB

FE -> Apache: POST /admin/updateUserStatus

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP user status update request
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found
    FE --> Admin: Display "User status update route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> UC: Pass validated and authorized status update request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> FE: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden / 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> Admin: Display validation or authorization error
end

UC -> UC: Validate status in ['Activo','Bloqueado']

alt Validation success
    UC -> ORM: Load target User model from route binding
else Validation failure
    UC --> FE: 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> Admin: Display invalid user status error
end

UC -> UC: previousStatus = user.status
UC -> ORM: user->save(status)
ORM -> DB: UPDATE users SET status = ? WHERE id = ?

alt User status update success
    DB --> ORM: Update successful
    ORM --> UC: User status persisted
else User status update failure
    DB --> ORM: Update failed / SQL exception
    ORM --> UC: User status persistence failed
    UC --> FE: 500 Internal Server Error
    FE --> Admin: Display system error while updating user status
end

UC -> ORM: User::where(role = 'Admin Super')->where(status = 'Activo')->first()
ORM -> DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE role = 'Admin Super' AND status = 'Activo' LIMIT 1

alt Super admin lookup success
    DB --> ORM: Active super admin record or empty result
    ORM --> UC: Super admin lookup result
else Super admin lookup failure
    DB --> ORM: Query failed / SQL exception
    ORM --> UC: Super admin lookup failed
    UC --> FE: 500 Internal Server Error
    FE --> Admin: Display system error while retrieving super admin contact
end

UC -> UC: superAdminEmail = superAdmin.email ?? fallback extension

alt Status changed to Bloqueado
    UC -> EmailService: send(user.email, "Cuenta bloqueada", blockedMessageWithContact)
    EmailService -> GenericMail: new GenericMail(subjectText, messageText)
    GenericMail --> EmailService: Mailable instance created
    EmailService -> Mailer: Mail::to(user.email)->queue(GenericMail)

    alt Email queued successfully
        Mailer -> Gmail: Deliver blocked account notification
        Gmail --> Mailer: Delivery accepted
        Mailer --> EmailService: Email queued/sent successfully
        EmailService --> UC: Block notification completed
    else Email queue/send failure
        Mailer --> EmailService: Queue / SMTP failure
        EmailService --> UC: Block notification failed
    end

else Status changed to Activo
    UC -> EmailService: send(user.email, "Cuenta desbloqueada", reactivatedMessage)
    EmailService -> GenericMail: new GenericMail(subjectText, messageText)
    GenericMail --> EmailService: Mailable instance created
    EmailService -> Mailer: Mail::to(user.email)->queue(GenericMail)

    alt Email queued successfully
        Mailer -> Gmail: Deliver account reactivated notification
        Gmail --> Mailer: Delivery accepted
        Mailer --> EmailService: Email queued/sent successfully
        EmailService --> UC: Reactivation notification completed
    else Email queue/send failure
        Mailer --> EmailService: Queue / SMTP failure
        EmailService --> UC: Reactivation notification failed
    end

else Status unchanged
    note right of UC: No email sent\npreviousStatus equals requested status
end

UC --> FE: Return JSON { success, message, status }
FE --> Admin: Show "Estado actualizado correctamente"

@enduml